<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="1034" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123So7/141</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-12T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3183. Your 3395 [3995], June 14, 4 p. m. and despatch 3363,<note n="1" xml:id="d1034fn1">Not printed.</note> June 14. Inform Foreign Office
                            that the proposal of the German Government, in accordance with the
                            treatment of consuls in Belgium, to grant to the American Consul at
                            Warsaw permission to exercise his consular functions in that part of his
                            consular district which is under German military occupation is
                            acceptable to United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>